:''See also'' [[Terror]]
==English==
===Pronunciation===
*{{SAMPA|/"tEr\@/}}

===Hyphenation===
:ter&middot;ror

===Etymology===
From Old French '''[[terreur]]''' (terror, fear, dread) < Latin accusative '''[[terrorem]]''' (fright, fear, terror) < Latin '''[[terrere]]''' (to frighten, terrify) < Proto-Indo-European base '''[[*tre-]]''' (to shake), '''[[*tres-]]''' (to tremble).

===Noun===
'''terror'''

# Extreme or intense [[fear]].
# Something that causes such fear.

